chapter two
fantasy edition

Kitsune is the Japanese term for a fox. In Japanese folklore, foxes are often featured in various stories as intelligent creatures whose magical abilities become more perfect as the fox gets wiser and older. In addition, all foxes can transform into a human male or female. In legend, foxes are often described as loyal guards, friends, lovers, or wives, although there are frequent stories of foxes deceiving humans.
